er emotions) communicated by the material and the body - have the potential to challenge or exceed existing relations of power in the mediascape. Wei Dong shows how Chinese reality TV provides a historical and theoretical opportunity for understanding the affective structures of contemporary China in the dynamic process of fracture and integration.  afunded by BMBF Fördervorhaben 16TOA002  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aChina. 4aCulture. 4aEmotion. 4aMedia Studies. 4aPopular Culture. 4aReality TV. 4aSociety. 4aSociology of Media. 4aTelevision. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Media Studies.2bisacsh  aChina.  aCulture.  aEmotion.  aMedia Studies.  aPopular Culture.  aReality TV.  aSociety.  aSociology of Media.  aTelevision.2 aBMBF Fördervorhaben 16TOA002efunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2z978311076700108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2022z9783111025094oZDB-23-TGP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript English Frontlist eBook-Package 2022z978311076851040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839462843?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839462843zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839462843/original  a978-3-11-076700-1 DG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2b2022  a978-3-11-076851-0 transcript English Frontlist eBook-Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA  aZDB-23-TGPb2022